Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
free_power_intent(25.10)                              free_power_intent(25.10)

Name
       free_power_intent  -  The  command  deletes  all  the power intent data
       stored by the commit_power_intent command in current session and cleans
       up the design

Syntax
       free_power_intent

       [-help]

       [-keep_fence]

       The command deletes all the  power  intent  data  stored  by  the  com-
       mit_power_intent command in current session and cleans up the design.

Parameters
       -help  Prints  a  brief  description that includes the type and default
              information for each free_power_intent parameter. For a detailed
              description of the command and all its parameters, use  the  man
              command:

              man free_power_intent

       -keep_fence
              Retains  domain  groups and their fences at the time of removing
              the the power intent. Use read_power_intent and commit_power_in-
              tent -keepRows to reload power intent after using  this  parame-
              ter.

Related Information
              * commit_power_intent

              * read_power_intent

              * write_power_intent

              * Low Power Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

